\textbf{Aims 1 \& 3 Manuscript:} Developing lipid pathway database with
ORA support \& user interface.

\textbf{Aim 2 \& 3 Manuscript}: Testing utility of consensus similarity networks
in identifying phenotype-dependent relationships between analytes \&
creating associated software.

\textbf{Conferences:} Preliminary results will be submitted to the American Society for Mass Spectrometry
 annual meeting as well as the annual Metabolomics Society meeting and the International Conference
 and Exhibition on Metabolomics \& Systems Biology. Annual internal presentation opportunities include
 the Ohio State University Cancer Care Center meeting, The Ohio Mass Spectrometry and Metabolomics
 Symposium (OMSMS), and the Biomedical Sciences Graduate Program Student Research Day.

\textbf{Career Development:} I am a member of the American Society for Mass
 Spectrometry, which provides many resources for career advancement
 through workshops and networking opportunities/resources hosted on
 their website. I am also a regular attendee of Friday afternoon
 luncheons with guest speakers hosted by the BMI department, which
 allows me to network with a wide variety of bioinformaticians both
 from OSU and elsewhere. OSU also offers career counseling services
 which I intend to take advantage of. Additionally I plan to get involved with
 early-career societies for metabolomics researchers, such as the
 Metabolomics Society Early-career Members Network.
